external_knowledge:
- "showered with high praise" refers to having a high average rating;
- "glowing reviews" refers to having at least 3 ratings;
- "stellar ratings" refers to the average rating.

- "stands atop the pedestal" refers to the brand with the highest rank or the best performance;
- "customer satisfaction" is measured by the average rating of the products;
- "highest average rating" means the brand with the greatest average rating.

- 'Highly Recommended' products have more than 50 ratings, an average user rating and average rating greater than 3.5, and a high inventory status;
- 'Recommended' products have more than 20 ratings, an average user rating and average rating greater than 3.0, and a high inventory status;
- 'Consider' products have more than 10 ratings, an average user rating and average rating greater than 2.5, and a high inventory status;
- 'Not Recommended' products do not meet the criteria for 'Highly Recommended', 'Recommended', or 'Consider'.

- 'Top 5' refers to the products with the highest average ratings;
- 'Most frequently gazed upon' refers to the products that have been ordered the most;
- 'Admired' refers to the quantity of the product that has been ordered.

- "American brands" refers to brands that originated in the USA;
- "earned the admiration of the masses" refers to products with an average rating above 3.5;
- "shining with an average rating above 3.5 stars" is a metaphorical way to describe a high average rating.

- "reaped the most bountiful harvest" refers to the brand generating the highest total revenue;
- "shining star" is a metaphor for the brand with the best performance;
- "grand marketplace of brands" is a metaphor for the competitive environment in which brands operate;
- "how much of their product has been sold" refers to the total quantity sold;
- "average rating bestowed upon their offerings" refers to the average rating of the products.

- 'Crown jewel' refers to the most valuable or important item in a collection;
- 'Treasure chest' is a metaphor for a repository of valuable items;
- 'Customer satisfaction' is represented by the average rating;
- 'Popularity' is represented by the total number of orders.

- 'average order quantity' is calculated by averaging the quantity of products ordered across all orders for a brand;
- 'total amount spent' is the sum of the total amounts of all orders for a brand;
- 'total revenue' is the sum of the product of the quantity and the price per item for all orders of a brand.

- 'High inventory' refers to products with more than 50 units in stock;
- 'High-rated' refers to products with an average rating greater than 4.0;
- 'Cotton' and 'Linen' are specific types of fabric materials.

- "boasts the crown" refers to being the top brand;
- "the most beloved and frequently purchased" indicates the product with the highest average rating and the highest number of orders;
- "top-rated product" means the product with the highest average rating within its brand.

- 'Best-selling styles' are determined by the total quantity of delivered orders;
- 'Average ratings' are calculated from customer ratings;
- 'Product descriptions' are provided for styles that have inventory levels above the reorder threshold.

- "In the garden of products" refers to the products table;
- "Blossoms have not withered" refers to products that are not discontinued (is_discontinued = 0);
- "Held in high regard" refers to products with high average ratings;
- "Shining brighter than 3.5 stars on average" refers to products with an average rating greater than 3.5.

- Average rating is a measure of customer satisfaction, typically ranging from 1 to 5 stars;
- Total revenue is the total amount of money generated from sales of the product;
- Price range indicates the cost of the product, which can influence its market performance;
- Brand name and style name are key identifiers that help in understanding the product's market position.

- "shone brighter than the average star in the sky" refers to products with an average rating higher than the overall average rating of all products;
- "favored by the earth" refers to products ordered more than 100 times;
- "garden of 2022" refers to the period between January 1, 2022, and December 31, 2022.
